 EVALUATION PROCEDURE                                             6425 1451
                                                                  6425 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                6425 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               6425 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             6425 1451
                                                                  6425 1451
 Available experimental data were interpreted  using              6425 1451
 nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-2.19b27 by                    6425 1451
 M. Herman et al [He01, He02]. This code integrates               6425 1451
 into a single system a number of important modules               6425 1451
 and features:                                                    6425 1451
                                                                  6425 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 6425 1451
   coupled-channels (ECIS03 by J. Raynal)                         6425 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    6425 1451
   HRTW width fluctuation correction                              6425 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                6425 1451
   TRISTAN by H. Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                      6425 1451
 - Exciton model with angular momentum coupling                   6425 1451
   (code DEGAS by E. Betak and P. Oblozinsky) that                6425 1451
   represents a good approximation to the DSD model               6425 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      6425 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 6425 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                6425 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   6425 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                6425 1451
   discrete transitions                                           6425 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL-2 library [Ri03]              6425 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                6425 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               6425 1451
   and gamma strength functions  based on the RIPL-2              6425 1451
   library [Ri03]                                                 6425 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              6425 1451
   EXFOR/CSISRS library                                           6425 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A. Trkov)                    6425 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 6425 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                6425 1451
   PrePro codes by R. Cullen                                      6425 1451
 - Checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                        6425 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               6425 1451
